#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:17
msgid "Getting started"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:19
msgid "There are two ways to setup AD/LDAP:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:21
msgid "Configure AD/LDAP using the System Console user interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:22
msgid ""
"Start the Mattermost server and create a new account using email and "
"password, which is assigned the System Administrator role as the first "
"user created, then configure AD/LDAP and then convert your System "
"Administrator account to use the AD/LDAP sign-in method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:23
msgid "Configure AD/LDAP by editing config.json"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:24
msgid ""
"Before starting the Mattermost server, edit config.json to enable AD/LDAP"
" based on AD/LDAP settings documentation. When you start the Mattermost "
"server the first user to log in with valid AD/LDAP credentials will be "
"assigned the System Administrator role."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:26
msgid "Configure AD/LDAP sign-in"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:28
msgid "After installing Mattermost:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:30
msgid ""
"Create a System Administrator account using email authentication. On a "
"new server create an account using email and password, which is "
"automatically assigned the System Administrator role since it is the "
"first account created. You may also assign the role to another account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:32
msgid ""
"Configure AD/LDAP. Go to System Console > AD/LDAP and fill in AD/LDAP "
"settings based on configuration settings documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:34
msgid ""
"Confirm AD/LDAP sign-on is enabled.  After AD/LDAP has been enabled, "
"confirm that users can sign in using AD/LDAP credentials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:36
msgid ""
"Switch your System Administrator account from email to AD/LDAP "
"authentication. Go to Account Settings > Security > Sign-in Method > "
"Switch to AD/LDAP and sign-in with your AD/LDAP credentials to complete "
"the switch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:38
msgid ""
"(Optional) Restrict authentication to AD/LDAP. Go to System Console > "
"Authentication > Email and set Allow Sign Up With Email to false and "
"Allow Sign In With Email to false. This should leave Active "
"Directory/LDAP as the only single sign-in option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:40
msgid ""
"(Optional) If you configured First Name Attribute and Last Name Attribute"
" in the System Console, go to System Console > General > Users and Teams "
"in prior versions or System Console > Site Configuration > Users and "
"Teams in versions after 5.12 and set Teammate Name Display to Show first "
"and last name. This is recommended for a better user experience."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:42
msgid ""
"If you've made a mistake and lock yourself out of the system somehow, you"
" can set an existing account to System Administrator using the "
"commandline tool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:44
msgid "Configure AD/LDAP synchronization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:46
msgid ""
"In addition to configuring AD/LDAP sign-in, you can also configure "
"AD/LDAP synchronization. When synchronizing, Mattermost queries AD/LDAP "
"for relevant account information and updates Mattermost accounts based on"
" changes to attributes (first name, last name, and nickname). When "
"accounts are disabled in AD/LDAP users are made inactive in Mattermost, "
"and their active sessions are revoked once Mattermost synchronizes "
"attributes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:48
msgid ""
"Note that the AD/LDAP sync depends on email. Make sure all users on your "
"AD/LDAP server have an email address or that their account is deactivated"
" in Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:50
msgid "To configure AD/LDAP synchronization with AD/LDAP sign-in:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:52
msgid ""
"Go to System Console > AD/LDAP and set Enable Synchronization with "
"AD/LDAP to true."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:53
msgid ""
"Set Syncronization Interval to specify how often Mattermost accounts "
"synchronize attributes with AD/LDAP. The default setting is 60 minutes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:55
msgid ""
"If you want to synchronize immediately after disabling an account, use "
"the \"AD/LDAP Synchronize Now\" button in System Console > AD/LDAP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:57
msgid ""
"Note: Make sure that at least 1 LDAP user is in Mattermost or the sync "
"will not complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:59
msgid ""
"To configure AD/LDAP synchronization with SAML sign-in, see the SAML "
"documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:61
msgid "Configure AD/LDAP deployments with multiple domains"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:63
msgid ""
"Organizations using multiple domains can integrate with Mattermost using "
"a \"Forest\" configuration to bring together multiple domains. Please see"
" Forests as Collections of Domain Controllers that Trust Each Other for "
"more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:65
msgid ""
"For forest configurations that contain multiple domains which do NOT "
"share a common root, you can search across all of the domains using the "
"Global Catalog. To do so, update your config.json as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:67
