#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:102
msgid ""
"What is the difference between the Username Attribute, ID Attribute and "
"Login ID Attribute?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:104
msgid ""
"There are three AD/LDAP attributes that apear to be similar but serve a "
"different purpose:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:106
msgid ""
"Username Attribute: Used within the Mattermost user interface to identify"
" and mention users. For example, if a Username Attribute is set to "
"john.smith, a user typing @john will see @john.smith in their auto-"
"complete options and posting a message with @john.smith will send a "
"notification to that user that theyâ€™ve been mentioned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:107
msgid ""
"ID Attribute: Used as the unique identifier in Mattermost. It should be "
"an AD/LDAP attribute with a value that does not change, such as "
"ObjectGUID. If a user's ID Attribute changes, it will create a new "
"Mattermost account unassociated with their old one. If you need to change"
" this field after users have already logged in, use the mattermost ldap "
"idmigrate CLI tool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-ldap.md:108
msgid ""
"Login ID Attribute: The attribute in the AD/LDAP server used to log in to"
" Mattermost. Normally this attribute is the same as the \"Username "
"Attribute\" field above, or another field that users can easily remember."
msgstr ""

